<sheet>
<description>Self-Test ardware</description>
<plain>
<text x="22.86" y="35.56" size="2.54" layer="97" align="bottom-center">REFERENCE
CLOCK (v4.0)</text>
<text x="215.9" y="10.16" size="4.445" layer="97" align="center">SELF-TEST HARDWARE</text>
<text x="261.62" y="10.16" size="3.81" layer="97" align="center">AR2</text>
<text x="152.4" y="177.8" size="2.54" layer="97" align="top-left">Desired Range: 0-27v
A6 (max) = Vbus * (R24 / (R23+R24))
A6 (max) = Vbus * (9.1K / (66.5K+9.1K) = 3.25 V
A6 resolution = A6 (max) / 4096 = 3.25 / 4096 = 0.656 V
</text>
<text x="147.32" y="185.42" size="3.81" layer="97" align="top-left">Calculations for Voltage Feedback:
</text>
<text x="88.9" y="114.3" size="3.81" layer="97" align="top-left">Calculations for Current Feedback:
</text>
<text x="91.44" y="106.68" size="2.54" layer="97" align="top-left">Desired Range: 0-2 A
INA180A1 Gain: 20 V/V
Rsense &lt; PDmax/ Imax * Imax
Rsense &lt; 1/4 Ω
Vsp = Vs - 0.03 V » 3.27
Vsn = Vgnd + 0.005 » 0.005
Vsp &gt; Imax * Rsense * Gain
Vsp &gt; 2 * 0.075 * 20 » 3 [OK]
Vsn &lt;  Imin * Rsense * Gain
Vsn &lt; 0 * 0.075 * 20 » 0 [OK]
A7 (max) = Imax * Rsense * Gain
A7 (max) = 2 * 0.075 * 20 » 3 V = 2 A
A7 resolution = A7 (max) / 4096 = 2 / 4096 = 0.5 mA per count
</text>
<text x="264.16" y="38.1" size="1.778" layer="97" align="bottom-right">*FILTER CAPACITORS FOR: X1, IC1</text>
<text x="40.64" y="45.72" size="3.81" layer="97" align="center-left">Testing with X1:
</text>
<text x="40.64" y="43.18" size="2.54" layer="97" align="top-left">X1 is used to validate the microprocessor timing.  Measure 
the number of pulses during a calculated amount of 
time, and verify it against the theoretical
value.  If the STM32 clock is accurate, then all of the 
timing will be correct.</text>
</plain>
