<sheet>
<description>Bidirectional Detection</description>
<plain>
<text x="243.84" y="66.04" size="1.778" layer="97" align="center">U9</text>
<wire x1="243.84" y1="68.58" x2="247.65" y2="68.58" width="0.1524" layer="94"/>
<wire x1="247.65" y1="68.58" x2="247.65" y2="63.5" width="0.1524" layer="94"/>
<wire x1="247.65" y1="63.5" x2="247.396" y2="63.5" width="0.1524" layer="94"/>
<wire x1="247.396" y1="63.5" x2="240.03" y2="63.5" width="0.1524" layer="94"/>
<wire x1="240.03" y1="63.5" x2="240.03" y2="68.58" width="0.1524" layer="94"/>
<wire x1="240.03" y1="68.58" x2="243.84" y2="68.58" width="0.1524" layer="94"/>
<text x="215.9" y="10.16" size="4.445" layer="97" align="center">BIDIRECTIONAL DETECTION</text>
<text x="261.62" y="10.16" size="3.81" layer="97" align="center">AR2</text>
<text x="109.22" y="101.6" size="3.81" layer="97" align="top-left">Calculations for Rsense:
</text>
<text x="111.76" y="195.58" size="2.54" layer="97" align="top-left">Desired Range: 0-0.165 mV
Attenuate: ~20:1
THRESH (max) = Avdd * (R25 / (R26+R25))
THRESH (max) = 3.3v * (10.2K / (191K+10.2K) = 0.167 mV
THRESH resolution = THRESH (max) / 4096 = 0.167 / 4096 = 40.7 nV
DAC Count for 19mV ~= 466 counts</text>
<text x="109.22" y="93.98" size="2.54" layer="97" align="top-left">Detector (min): &lt; 6 mA
Detector (max): 34 mA @ 200 mV
Rsense (max): 5 Ω
Max of (2) Detectors in loop.</text>
<text x="111.76" y="200.66" size="3.81" layer="97" align="top-left">Calculations for Detector Threshold:
</text>
<text x="264.16" y="40.64" size="1.778" layer="97" align="bottom-right">*FILTER CAPACITORS FOR: IC5, IC6, IC7</text>
<text x="71.12" y="154.94" size="2.54" layer="97" align="center">PLACE R31 OR IC7/C23.</text>
<text x="2.54" y="2.54" size="2.54" layer="97" ratio="12">BRIEF THEORY OF OPERATION

DURING THE CUTOUT, THE H-BRIDGE IS DISABLED (BR_ENABLE = 0), AND THE 
DETECTOR IS ENABLED (BIDIR_EN = 1).  Q5 IS TURNED ON, Q5 IS TURNED 
OFF, AND Q1A &amp; Q1B ARE TURNED
 ON.   
BIDIR CURRENT FLOWS FROM THE DECODER VIA TRK_A THROUGH R 15 &amp; R7 TO 
TRK_B AND BACK TO THE DECODER, OR VICE-VERSA.
THE VOLTAAGE DROP ACROSS R15/R7 IS FILTERED BY R19/C25 AND R20/C24 
AND FED TO U9.    THE DAC OUTPUT OF THE MICROPROCESSOR SETS THE 
DESIRED SENSE THRESHOLD VOLTAGE.
THE OUTPUTS OF U9 ARE FED INTO U10; WHEN EITHER IS LOW, U10'S OUTPUT
 IS LOW.  THAT SIGNAL IS FED BACK TO THE MICROPROCESSOR UART6, AND A 
TBD TIMER PIN.</text>
<wire x1="2.54" y1="50.8" x2="60.96" y2="50.8" width="0.1524" layer="97"/>
<text x="116.84" y="109.22" size="1.778" layer="91">HIGH for cutout</text>
<text x="76.2" y="99.06" size="1.778" layer="91">LOw 
for 
cutout</text>
<text x="226.06" y="149.86" size="1.778" layer="97" ratio="11" align="center-left">(USART10_RX</text>
<text x="226.06" y="165.1" size="1.778" layer="97" ratio="11" align="center-left">(USART6_RX</text>
<text x="218.44" y="156.718" size="1.778" layer="97" ratio="11">NOTE: Need comments on USART 
timing and voltage levels.</text>
<wire x1="215.9" y1="162.56" x2="215.9" y2="154.94" width="0.1524" layer="97"/>
<wire x1="215.9" y1="154.94" x2="264.16" y2="154.94" width="0.1524" layer="97"/>
